# === SUITE 6 GOVERNANCE RULES ===
# Auto-loaded by Cursor for governance compliance
# Source: Cursor Governance Suite 6 (L9 + Suite 5)

## Core Governance Principles
- Always use Suite 6 canonical headers for governance files
- Follow kebab-case naming convention for prompt files (briefs/summaries/reports remain in CAPS)
- Integrate with formal logic system for rule validation
- Maintain audit trails for all governance decisions
- Use cross-layer integration patterns

## File Standards
- Governance files must have canonical headers with complete metadata
- Component IDs must follow pattern: [LAYER-DOMAIN-###]
- All files should be self-documenting with clear purpose statements
- Integration points must be explicitly documented

## Development Workflow
- Use @.cursor-commands/ to access governance components
- Validate compliance before commits
- Follow 10-step reasoning framework for technical decisions
- Integrate with meta-learning system for continuous improvement

## API Integration
- Use governance API endpoints for programmatic access
- Follow REST conventions with proper error handling
- Include governance metadata in API responses
- Maintain performance targets (<200ms response time)

## Security and Compliance
- All governance files require audit trails
- Security classification must be specified
- Follow escalation procedures for policy violations
- Maintain compliance metrics and reporting

## Suite 6 Components Access
- Intelligence: @.cursor-commands/intelligence/
- Foundation: @.cursor-commands/foundation/
- Execution: @.cursor-commands/execution/
- Operations: @.cursor-commands/operations/
- Environment: @.cursor-commands/environment/
- Telemetry: @.cursor-commands/telemetry/

For detailed guidance, see: @.cursor-commands/intelligence/reasoning/cursor-native-reasoning.md

